// for checked exceptions, you can:
// either specify, in the method definition, which exceptions can be caught (using "throws <exception_name>")
// or insert a "try...catch" block inside the method body

//In either case, for custom exceptions you need to throw manually the exception when required, with "throw new <exception_name>"
